### Retrieve a Task [GET /tasks/{id}]

The "taskStatus" task return attribute has the following return values:

* Opened = 1
* InDisplacement = 2
* CheckedIn = 3
* CheckedOut = 4
* Finished = 5
* Paused = 6

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    [Task][]

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "id": [
                    "The value 'x' is not valid."
                ]
            }

+ Response 404

### Add a new Task [POST /tasks/]

The body example describes the minimum required attributes to successfully add a task. See the **Attributes** or **Json Schema** in the Example section for all allowed attributes.

The task address will preferably be obtained through the client's address.
If the customer ID was not informed, the data will be captured by the parameters of the register itself.
When the latitude and longitude are not informed, the Auvo API will attempt to obtain this information through the address you provided.

+ Attributes
    + externalId (string) - External task id. Max 255 characters
    + taskType (number) - taskTypeId of the task type
    + idUserFrom (required, number) - userId of the User that is opening the task
    + idUserTo (number) - userId of the User responsible for executing the task
    + listIdUserTo (array[number]) - List of userIds to create multiple tasks
    + teamId (number) - Existing team id at Auvo
    + taskDate (string) - Date and time for the execution of the task. Format: "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss"
    + latitude (number) - Latitude of the task
    + longitude (number) - Longitude of the task
    + address (string) - Address of the task
    + orientation (required, string) - Orientation of the task. Max 5000 characters
    + priority (required, number) - Priority of the task. 1 - Low | 2 - Medium | 3 - High
    + questionnaireId (number) - QuestionnaireId of the CheckList included in the task
    + customerId (number) - CustomerId of the Customer chosen for the task
    + checkinType (number) - Checkin type. 1 - Manual | 2 - Automatic | 3 - User
    + attachments (array)
        + name (required, string) - The name MUST contain the file type (Ex. "my_file.pdf")
        + file (required, string) - Base 64 file
    + keyWords (array[string]) - List of keywords id
    + equipmentsId (array[number]) - List of equipment ids
    + sendSatisfactionSurvey (boolean) - Send satisfaction survey for the task
    + sendDigitalOs (boolean) - Send digital OS for the task
    + taskProducts (array)
        + productId (required, string) - ProductId (GUID) attribute of the Product
        + code (number) - Product code
        + discountType (number) - 0 - monetary value | 1 - percentage
        + discountValue (number) - Discount value in decimal format
        + quantity (required, number) - Quantity in decimal format
        + value (required, number) - Unit value in decimal format
    + taskServices (array)
        + serviceId (required, string) - Service Id (GUID)
        + discountType (number) - 0 - monetary value | 1 - percentage
        + discountValue (number) - Discount value in decimal format
        + quantity (required, number) - Quantity in decimal format
        + value (required, number) - Unit value in decimal format
    + taskAdditionalCosts (array)
        + additionalCostId (required, string) - AdditionalCostId (GUID)
        + value (required, number) - Unit value in decimal format
    + taskDiscount (object)
        + type (required, number) - 0 - monetary value | 1 - percentage
        + value (required, number) - Discount value in decimal format
    + financialCategory (string) - Name of the Financial Category
    + financialCategoryId (string) - GUID of the Financial Category

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                "externalId": "123",
                "taskType": 1,
                "idUserFrom": 99,
                "idUserTo": 69,
                "teamId": 6,
                "taskDate": "2016-04-23T18:00:00",
                "latitude": -16.6872086111083,
                "longitude": -49.2995542287827,
                "address": "avenue Y",
                "orientation": "Task orientation",
                "priority": 1,
                "questionnaireId": 3,
                "customerId": 1,
                "checkinType": 1,
                "sendSatisfactionSurvey": false,
                "sendDigitalOs": false,
                "attachments": [
                    {
                        "name": "my_file.pdf",
                        "file": "base64 encoded file"
                    }
                ],
                "keyWords": ["1"],
                "equipmentsId": [109638],
                "taskProducts": [
                    {
                        "productId": "63867f52-b262-410a-a409-cc25ba92ded1",
                        "quantity": 2,
                        "value": 10.50,
                        "discountType": 0,
                        "discountValue": 1.00
                    }
                ],
                "taskServices": [
                    {
                        "serviceId": "63867f52-b262-410a-a409-cc25ba92ded1",
                        "quantity": 1,
                        "value": 50.00
                    }
                ],
                "taskAdditionalCosts": [
                    {
                        "additionalCostId": "63867f52-b262-410a-a409-cc25ba92ded1",
                        "value": 5.00
                    }
                ],
                "taskDiscount": {
                    "type": 0,
                    "value": 2.00
                },
                "financialCategory": "Category Name"
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            "result": {
                "taskID": 123,
                "externalId": "123",
                "idUserFrom": 99,
                "idUserTo": 69,
                "customerId": 1,
                "taskType": 1,
                "creationDate": "2019-04-03T13:06:09",
                "taskDate": "2016-04-23T18:00:00",
                "latitude": -16.6872086111083,
                "longitude": -49.2995542287827,
                "address": "avenue Y",
                "orientation": "Task orientation",
                "priority": 1,
                "deliveredOnSmarthPhone": false,
                "finished": false,
                "checkinType": 1,
                "keyWords": ["1"],
                "attachments": [],
                "questionnaires": [],
                "signatureUrl": "",
                "checkInDistance": 0,
                "checkOutDistance": 0,
                "sendSatisfactionSurvey": false,
                "taskStatus": 1
            }

### Upsert - Add a new Task or update an existing one [PUT /tasks/]
Update or register a new task according to one of its identifier, `id` OR `externalId`. If there is no task with the provided identifier, create a new task, if it exists, update it. Returns HTTP status code 200 if the task was updated and 201 if it was created.

+ Attributes
    + id (number) - The task id (used as identifier for upsert)
    + externalId (string) - External task id (used as identifier for upsert)
    + taskType (number) - taskTypeId of the task type
    + idUserFrom (required, number) - userId of the User that is opening the task
    + idUserTo (number) - userId of the User responsible for executing the task
    + listIdUserTo (array[number]) - List of userIds to create multiple tasks
    + teamId (number) - Existing team id at Auvo
    + taskDate (string) - Date and time. Format: "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss"
    + latitude (number) - Latitude of the task
    + longitude (number) - Longitude of the task
    + address (string) - Address of the task
    + orientation (required, string) - Orientation of the task. Max 5000 characters
    + priority (required, number) - 1 - Low | 2 - Medium | 3 - High
    + questionnaireId (number) - QuestionnaireId of the CheckList
    + customerId (number) - CustomerId of the Customer
    + checkinType (number) - 1 - Manual | 2 - Automatic | 3 - User
    + sendSatisfactionSurvey (boolean)
    + sendDigitalOs (boolean)
    + financialCategory (string) - Financial Category name
    + financialCategoryId (string) - Financial Category GUID

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                "externalId": "123",
                "taskType": 1,
                "idUserFrom": 99,
                "idUserTo": 69,
                "taskDate": "2016-04-23T18:00:00",
                "address": "avenue Y",
                "orientation": "Task orientation",
                "priority": 1
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

+ Response 201 (application/json)

### Edit a Task [PATCH /tasks/{id}]
To update a `Task`, send a JSONPatchDocument with updated value for one or more of the `TaskPatch` attributes.
JsonPatch example: { "op": "replace", "path": "orientation", "value": "New orientation" }

+ Attributes
    + taskType (number) - Task type id
    + externalId (string) - External task id
    + idUserFrom (number) - User id that opened the task
    + idUserTo (number) - User id responsible for executing
    + teamId (number) - Team id
    + taskDate (string) - "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss"
    + latitude (number) - Task latitude
    + longitude (number) - Task longitude
    + address (string) - Task address
    + orientation (string) - Task orientation
    + priority (number) - 1 - Low | 2 - Medium | 3 - High
    + questionnaireId (number) - Questionnaire id
    + customerId (number) - Customer id
    + checkinType (number) - 1 - Manual | 2 - Automatic | 3 - User
    + keyWords (array[string]) - List of keywords id
    + sendSatisfactionSurvey (boolean)
    + sendDigitalOs (boolean)
    + financialCategory (string) - Financial Category name
    + financialCategoryId (string) - Financial Category GUID

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            [
                { "op": "replace", "path": "orientation", "value": "New orientation" }
            ]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    [Task][]

### Upsert Task Attachments [PUT /tasks/{id}/attachments]
Add or replace attachments on a task.

+ Attributes
    + removeAllAttachmentsInsertedByMe (boolean) - Remove all attachments previously inserted by the API before adding new ones
    + attachments (array)
        + name (required, string) - File name with extension (Ex. "my_file.pdf")
        + file (required, string) - Base 64 file

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                "removeAllAttachmentsInsertedByMe": false,
                "attachments": [
                    {
                        "name": "photo.jpg",
                        "file": "base64 encoded file"
                    }
                ]
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    [Task][]

