# Group WebHooks

## WebHook [/webhooks/{id}]

+ Parameters

    + id (number) ... `id` of the webhook.

### Retrieve a WebHook [GET /webhooks/{id}]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            "result": {
                "id": 1,
                "entity": "User",
                "action": "Inclusao",
                "urlResponse": "https://your-url.com/webhook",
                "creationDate": "2024-01-01 14:30:45",
                "deleteDate": null,
                "active": true
            }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "message": "The id is required",
                "errors": ["The id is required"]
            }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "errorCode": 1027,
                "message": "Webhook not found."
            }

### Add a new WebHook [POST /webhooks/]

If the `id` is provided and a webhook with that id already exists, the webhook will be updated instead of created. Returns HTTP status code 200 if updated and 201 if created.

**Entity values:**
* 1 - User
* 4 - Task
* 7 - Customer
* 27 - Equipment
* 50 - Invoice
* 62 - Ticket

**Action values:**
* 1 - Inclusao (Creation)
* 2 - Alteracao (Modification)
* 3 - Exclusao (Deletion)

+ Attributes
    + id (number) - Webhook id. Use 0 for new, or existing id to update
    + entity (required, number) - Entity type: 1-User | 4-Task | 7-Customer | 27-Equipment | 50-Invoice| 62-Ticket
    + action (required, number) - Action type: 1-Inclusao | 2-Alteracao | 3-Exclusao
    + targetUrl (required, string) - Target webhook URL. Max 250 characters
    + active (boolean) - Active status

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                "id": 0,
                "entity": 1,
                "action": 1,
                "targetUrl": "https://your-url.com/webhook",
                "active": true
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            "result": {
                "id": 1,
                "entity": "User",
                "action": "Inclusao",
                "urlResponse": "https://your-url.com/webhook",
                "creationDate": "2024-01-01 14:30:45",
                "deleteDate": null,
                "active": true
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            "result": {
                "id": 1,
                "entity": "User",
                "action": "Alteracao",
                "urlResponse": "https://your-url.com/webhook-updated",
                "creationDate": "2024-01-01 14:30:45",
                "deleteDate": null,
                "active": true
            }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "errorCode": 1026,
                "message": "Webhook with the given entity already registered for this admin user."
            }

### Delete a WebHook [DELETE /webhooks/{id}]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

+ Response 204

### Retrieve a list of WebHooks [GET /webhooks/?paramFilter={paramFilter}&page={page}&pageSize={pageSize}&order={order}]

+ Parameters
    + paramFilter (optional, string) ... JSON encoded string filter.
        + id (number) - Webhook id
        + entity (number) - Entity type: 1-User | 4-Task | 7-Customer | 27-Equipment | 50-Invoice| 62-Ticket
        + action (number) - Action type: 1-Inclusao | 2-Alteracao | 3-Exclusao
        + active (boolean) - Active status filter
    + page (required, number) ... Page. Default 1.
    + pageSize (required, number) ... Records per page. Default 10.
    + order (required, string) ... "asc"/0 or "desc"/1.

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "result": {
                "entityList": [
                    {
                        "id": 1,
                        "entity": "User",
                        "action": "Inclusao",
                        "urlResponse": "https://your-url.com/webhook",
                        "creationDate": "2024-01-01 14:30:45",
                        "deleteDate": null,
                        "active": true
                    }
                ],
                "pagedSearchReturnData": {
                    "order": 0,
                    "pageSize": 10,
                    "page": 1,
                    "totalItems": 1
                },
                "links": []
            }
        }

